      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANYA IGNITE (1) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 3.5 lengths from the winner (19.73). Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Can bounce back. COSMIC REWARD (6) turned in a plain performance last time when sixth at this track over 425m behind Bayini (24.92) in a Grade 5. Expected to give a good account. ELITE DARA (2) turned in a better effort at Shepparton last start, finishing second behind Berringa Paddy (22.93) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Hard to beat again. BROOMBRAE FRITZ (8) is a last-start placegetter from this box - in the mix again.",
